<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2015/07/13/spring-io-platform-1-1-3-released">Spring IO Platform 1.1.3 released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/8d143bf6d465cb98f8196cf4311256d0?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/awilkinson">Andy Wilkinson</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-07-13 19:35:06.734">July 13, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2187" href="/blog/2015/07/13/spring-io-platform-1-1-3-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>We are pleased to announce that <a href="https://platform.spring.io/platform">Spring IO Platform</a> 1.1.3.RELEASE is now available from both <a href="https://repo.spring.io/release">repo.spring.io</a> and <a href="https://search.maven.org/#search%7Cga%7C1%7Cg%3Aio.spring.platform">Maven Central</a>. </p>
<p>This maintenance release upgrades the versions of a number of the projects in the Platform to pick up their latest maintenance releases:</p>
<ul>
<li>Spring AMQP 1.4.5</li>
<li>Spring Batch 3.0.4</li>
<li>Spring Boot 1.2.5</li>
<li>Spring Data Evans SR3</li>
<li>Spring Framework 4.1.7</li>
<li>Spring Integration 4.1.5</li>
<li>Spring LDAP 2.0.3</li>
<li>Spring Mobile 1.1.4</li>
<li>Spring Session 1.0.1</li>
<li>Spring Social 1.1.2</li>
<li>Spring Social Facebook 2.0.1</li>
</ul>
<p>The versions of many third-party dependencies have also been updated.</p>
</div>
</section>
